# rs_audio_stats

üéµ Professional-grade audio analysis and normalization library for Python with EBU R128 loudness measurement.

[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/rs-audio-stats.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/rs-audio-stats/)
[![Python versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/rs-audio-stats.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/rs-audio-stats/)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-green.svg)](LICENSE)

## ‚ú® Features

- **üìä EBU R128 Loudness Analysis**: Industry-standard loudness measurement (¬±0.05 LUFS accuracy)
- **üéõÔ∏è Audio Normalization**: Normalize to broadcast standards (-23 LUFS, streaming platforms)
- **‚ö° High Performance**: SIMD-optimized, multi-threaded batch processing
- **üîÑ Batch Processing**: Analyze entire directories with progress tracking
- **üìÅ Multiple Formats**: WAV, FLAC, MP3, AAC, OGG, ALAC, MP4/M4A support
- **üì§ Export Options**: CSV, JSON, XML, TSV output formats
- **üåç Cross-Platform**: Windows, macOS (Intel/Apple Silicon), Linux - **No Rust required!**

## üöÄ Quick Start

```bash
pip install rs-audio-stats
```

```python
import rs_audio_stats

# Analyze audio file
info, results = rs_audio_stats.analyze_audio_all("audio.wav")
print(f"Loudness: {results.integrated_loudness:.1f} LUFS")
print(f"Peak: {results.true_peak:.1f} dBFS")

# Normalize to streaming standard
rs_audio_stats.normalize_to_lufs("input.wav", -14.0, "output.wav")
```

